      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO : DIRECTOR, FBI DATE: July 18, 1947",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, NEW HAVEN",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "67c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: \"FLYING SAUCERS\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "EDWIN M. BAILEY, JR.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "STAMFORD, CONNECTICUT, INFORMANT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "ATOMIC ENERGY ACT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "For the information of the Bureau this is to advise that on July 7, 1947,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "[REDACTED] Stamford, Connecticut, appeared at the 67c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "Stamford Resident Agent's office and furnished the following information:-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "[REDACTED] prefaced his remarks by stating that he is a scientist by",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "occupation and is currently employed at the American Cyanamid Research",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Laboratories on West Main Street in Stamford, Connecticut, in the Physics 67c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "Division. [REDACTED] further indicated that during the war he was employed",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "at MIT, Cambridge, Massachusetts, in the Radiation Laboratory which labora-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "tory is connected with the Manhattan Project. [REDACTED] advised that he is",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "thirty years of age and is a graduate of the University of Arizona.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "[REDACTED] stated that the topic of \"flying saucers\" had caused considerable",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "comment and concern to the present day scientists and indicated that he him-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "self had a personal theory concerning the \"flying saucers\". Prior to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "advancing his own theory, [REDACTED] remarked that immediately after the conclu-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "sion of World War II, a friend of his, [REDACTED] allegedly observed",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "the \"flying saucers\" from an observatory in Milan and Bologna, Italy. He",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "stated that apparently at that time the \"flying saucers\" had caused a little",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "comment in Italy but that after some little publicity they immediately died 67c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "out as public interest. [REDACTED] stated that it is quite possible that",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "actually the \"flying saucers\" could be radio controlled germ bombs or atom",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "bombs which are circling the orbit of the earth and which could be controlled",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "by radio and directed to land on any designated target at the specific desire",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "of the agency or country operating the bombs. He stated that one of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "items of interest which he personally has observed is the fact that the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "saucers have been observed in Mexico City, New Orleans, Philadelphia, New",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "York, Boston, Halifax, Newfoundland, Paris, Milan, Bologna and Yugoslavia",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "as well as Albania. By placing a string around the globe of the earth it",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "[unclear]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
